Private Events & Weddings
/.hero-image
Make Your Special Day Truly Memorable
At Lely Resort Golf & Country Club, we specialize in creating one-of-a-kind weddings and special events of all sizes and types that reflect your personal style and create memories to last a lifetime. From small, intimate business dinners and corporate meetings to fundraising events, golf tournaments, and holiday parties, we offer unrivaled amenities and comprehensive event management services, all underscored by unparalleled service.
Contact Us
Host Your Next Event
Weddings & Receptions
Accomodating groups from 125 for a seated dinner to 250 for a cocktail reception, the elegant Classics Dining Room is the ideal choice for hosting unforgettable wedding receptions. Featuring floor-to-ceiling windows and spectacular views of the championship golf course and our beautiful sparkling fountain, the Classics Dining Room can easily be set up for your special event.
Wedding ceremonies, vow renewals, and other events can also be held in a variety of stunning indoor and outdoor venues. Our clubhouse serves as a picturesque locale for larger wedding receptions. Smaller receptions and wedding functions including bridal showers, rehearsal dinners and bachelor/bachelorette parties can be held in our intimate dining room.
Parties & Celebrations
The only thing better than our breathtaking setting and world-class amenities is our attention to detail.  We pride ourselves on delivering truly memorable events of all types and sizes, with packages that are affordable and customizable.
Corporate Events
Replace the traditional board meeting with an exhilarating round of golf on one of our magnificent championship layouts; the usual coffee break with a lesson at our 54,000 sq. ft. driving range and expansive practice facility, a perfect venue for inspiring team-building and forging lasting business relationships. From small business meetings to large corporate functions, we have the amenities, event capabilities, and service to ensure your event is flawlessly-executed and truly unforgettable.

Membership
/.hero-image
A SENSE OF COMMUNITY, CAMARADERIE, AND BELONGING.
Outstanding privileges and amenities are just as important as the intangible benefits that come with private club membership.  We offer a variety of affordable membership options at The Classics Country Club that gives you both: access to three of the region’s most memorable golf layouts, along with a year-long schedule of exclusive events tailored to engage and delight every member of the family.
Schedule a Tour
Membership Options
Whether you are seeking a place to relax with family and friends or an unmatched venue for client entertainment, you’ve come to the right place. We also offer members the opportunity to join The National Golf Club – extending your membership privileges to golf courses across the U.S. Please contact our Director of Sales for more information or to inquire about our new member incentive offers.
Email
[email protected]
or call
(239) 732-1200
today!
FULL GOLF
Members, their spouse, and children up to the age of 23 enjoy an array of outstanding privileges including full golf access to The Classics and preferred tee times on The Flamingo and The Mustang courses.
Members enjoy full club privileges, including:
54-holes of championship golf designed by Gary Player, Robert Trent Jones, Sr. and Lee Trevino.
Two clubhouses, each with a full driving range, short game practice areas and putting greens.
Private clubhouse featuring a formal dining room, golf shop and members’ lounge.
Men’s and women’s locker rooms, each with its own lounge.
Bag storage and inter-club transportation of bags.
Golf carts-equipped with GPS course navigation system.
Two Har-Tru clay tennis courts and two pickleball courts.
Fitness center with aerobics studio, weight room and cardio workout area.
PGA golf instructors and USTPA-certified tennis professional.
Personal trainers and massage therapist.
Full calendar of golf and social events throughout the year.
Executive Membership
Members up to the age of 45, their spouses, and children up to the age of 23 enjoy an array of outstanding privileges, including full golf access to The Classics and preferred tee times on The Flamingo and The Mustang courses.
Members enjoy full club privileges, including:
54-holes of championship golf designed by Gary Player, Robert Trent Jones, Sr. and Lee Trevino.
Two clubhouses, each with a full driving range, short game practice areas and putting greens.
Private clubhouse featuring a formal dining room, golf shop and members’ lounge.
Men’s and women’s locker rooms, each with its own lounge.
Bag storage and inter-club transportation of bags.
Golf carts-equipped with GPS course navigation system.
Two Har-Tru tennis courts.
Fitness center with aerobics studio, weight room and cardio workout area.
PGA golf instructors and USTPA-certified tennis professional.
Personal trainers and massage therapist.
Full calendar of golf and social events throughout the year.
Social Sport Membership
Members, their spouse, and children up to the age of 23 enjoy full access to the clubhouse, tennis facilities, and fitness center, as well as a full calendar of social events.  Members may also play golf on all three courses May through October.
54 holes of championship golf designed by Gary Player, Robert Trent Jones, Sr., and Lee Trevino from May to October.
Two clubhouses, each with a full driving range, short game practice areas, and putting greens.
Private clubhouse featuring a formal dining room, golf shop and members’ lounge.
Golf carts equipped with GPS course navigation system.
Two Har-Tru clay tennis courts.
Fitness center with aerobics studio, weight room, and cardio workout area.
PGA golf instructors and USTPA-certified tennis professional on-site.
Personal trainers and massage therapist.
Social Membership
Members, their spouse, and children up to the age of 23 enjoy the facilities and amenities of The Classics and invitations to exclusive member-only events.
Social members enjoy full access to:
Private clubhouse featuring a formal dining room, golf shop and members’ lounge.
Men’s and women’s locker rooms, each with its own lounge.
Fitness center with aerobics studio, weight room and cardio workout area.
Personal trainers and massage therapist.
Full calendar of social events throughout the year.
Member Benefits
Palmer Advantage
Palmer Advantage offers access, member-only pricing, and unique opportunities you can’t find anywhere else.
MEMBER ADVANTAGE PLAN
Our members also receive our exclusive Member Advantage Plan, which provides multiple privileges and value-added benefits to membership. With the Member Advantage Plan, you will enjoy a variety of outstanding benefits and privileges including discounts on merchandise and special events, complimentary golf clinics, and much more!
Member Advantage Plan Details:
Extend the privileges of your membership with our exclusive Member Advantage Plan.
No Assessments:
Enjoy premier facilities and services – without assessment fees.
Leave a Legacy:
Share the privilege of membership with selected family members.
Transfer Your Membership:
Transfer your membership fee to clubs in our nationwide network if you move.
Complimentary Clinics:
Access complimentary golf clinics for members of all ages and abilities.
Merchandise Discounts:
Purchase pro shop merchandise at significantly reduced pricing.
Special Event Pricing:
Get special pricing on food and beverage selections, plus no room rental fees.
For more information, please call the Membership Director at
(239) 732-1200
or email
[email protected]
.

Expand your membership to include The National Golf Club and have full access to golf and social privileges at 150+ exceptional golf courses.
